{
  "text": "Nasopharyngeal carcinoma (NPC) is a rare tumor derived from nasopharyngeal epithelium [CITATION_1] , most of which are poorly differentiated squamous cell carcinomas [CITATION_2] . NPC is prevalent in east Africa and Asia, especially southern China, with the incidence rate of up to 0.2% [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . According to epidemiological studies, the occurrence of NPC may be closely related to genetic factors, environmental factors, and Epstein-Barr Virus (EBV) infection [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . People of smoke, alcohol abuse, and exposure to dangerous chemicals show higher risk of NPC [CITATION_7] . Until now, the treatment of NPC still remains as the greatest obstacle, due to the high rate of metastasis [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . Thus, elucidating the mechanisms and screening biomarkers for early diagnosis show great clinical significance.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "29386555",
